🧑‍💻 Jenkins Freestyle CI/CD Project (Assignment 1)

This project demonstrates automation using Jenkins Freestyle Jobs for Git operations, file creation, and deployment with integrated notifications using Slack and Email.

📌 Overview

The assignment is divided into two parts:

Part 1: Git branch automation using Jenkins Freestyle Job
Part 2: Parameterized file creation and web deployment using chained Jenkins Freestyle Jobs

All jobs include:

Automated execution
Error handling
Slack notifications
Email notifications
⚙️ Tools Used
Jenkins (Freestyle Jobs)
Git / Git Bash
Linux (Ubuntu/CentOS)
Apache Web Server
Slack Webhook Integration
SMTP Email Service
🚀 Part 1: Git Branch Automation (Freestyle Job)
🎯 Objective

Automate Git operations using Jenkins Freestyle Job.

🔧 Job Configuration
Job Type: Freestyle Project
Source Code Management: Git
Build Step: Execute Shell
🧠 Operations Performed

The Jenkins job performs:

Create a branch
List all branches
Merge branches
Rebase branches
Delete a branch
📜 Shell Script Used
git checkout -b feature-branch
git branch
git checkout main
git merge feature-branch
git rebase feature-branch
git branch -d feature-branch
