🚀 Part 2: Parameterized File + Web Deployment (Freestyle Jobs)
🎯 Objective

Create a file using Jenkins parameter and publish it using a web server.

🧩 Job 1: File Creation Job
🔹 Configuration
Job Type: Freestyle Project
Parameter: String → Ninja Name
🧠 Task Performed

Creates a file and adds content:

<Ninja Name> from DevOps Ninja
📜 Shell Script
echo "${NINJA_NAME} from DevOps Ninja" > ninja.txt
📸 Screenshots

👉 Jenkins parameter configuration

📸 [Insert Image 5: Build Parameter Setup Screen]

👉 Console output of file creation

📸 [Insert Image 6: File Created Output]

🧩 Job 2: Web Server Deployment Job
🔹 Configuration
Job Type: Freestyle Project
Trigger: Build after Job 1 (Upstream Job)
🧠 Task Performed
Copies file to web server directory
Publishes content on browser
📜 Shell Script
sudo cp ninja.txt /var/www/html/index.html
sudo systemctl restart apache2
📸 Screenshots

👉 Job trigger configuration (Upstream/Downstream)

📸 [Insert Image 7: Jenkins Job Trigger Setup]

👉 Web server output in browser

📸 [Insert Image 8: Browser Output - Deployed Page]

🔗 Job Flow Diagram
Job 1 (Create File with Parameter)
          ↓ (Success)
Job 2 (Deploy on Web Server)
          ↓
Slack + Email Notifications
🚨 Notifications Setup
On Failure:
Slack alert (error stage)
Email alert (build failure details)
On Success:
Slack success message
Email success confirmation
📌 Conclusion

This project successfully demonstrates:

Jenkins Freestyle Job automation
Git branch operations
Parameterized builds
Web deployment using Apache
CI/CD job chaining
Slack & Email notifications

